ble-content"><div dir=3D"auto" class=3D"body markup"><p>William Costello is=
 a rising star in the field of evolutionary psychology, and one of the few =
scholars seriously studying incel communities. He is a PhD student at the U=
niversity of Texas at Austin, where he is a member of Dr. David Buss' Evolu=
tionary Psychology lab.</p><p><span>Today William and I spoke about incels,=
 male adolescence, and what=E2=80=99s actually going on with disaffected yo=
ung men today. His research is truly fascinating. I strongly recommend foll=
owing William on Twitter/X </span><a href=3D"https://x.com/CostelloWilliam"=
 rel=3D"">here</a><span>.</span></p><p>Some topics we covered:</p><ul><li><=
p><span>Fascinating findings from William Costello=E2=80=99s </span><a href=
=3D"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s40806-022-00336-x" rel=3D"">=
research</a><span>: </span></p><ul><li><p>73% of incels meet the criteria f=
or moderate or severe depression vs. 33% of non-incels</p></li><li><p>67% o=
f incels were severely or moderately anxious vs. 38% of non-incels</p></li>=
<li><p><span>His research </span><a href=3D"https://www.gov.uk/government/p=
ublications/predicting-harm-among-incels-involuntary-celibates/predicting-h=
arm-among-incels-involuntary-celibates-the-roles-of-mental-health-ideologic=
al-belief-and-social-networking-accessible" rel=3D"">suggests</a><span> tha=
t about one-third of incels qualify for an autism diagnosis</span></p></li>=
<li><p>More than 50% have had suicidal thoughts in the past two weeks</p></=
li></ul></li><li><p>One of the biggest myths is that incels are white, righ=
t-wing extremists. In fact, 42% of incels are ethnic minorities.</p></li><l=
i><p>Politically, incels lean center-left on average which complicates the =
usual narrative. We both agreed that incels aren=E2=80=99t a political move=
ment. They don=E2=80=99t have a coherent ideology=E2=80=94just a shared des=
pair around sex, status, and rejection.</p></li><li><p><span>Netflix=E2=80=
=99s </span><em>Adolescence</em><span>=E2=80=94a gripping miniseries about =
a troubled teenage boy=E2=80=94and broke down what the show gets right (and=
 wrong) about modern teenage masculinity.</span></p></li><li><p>William poi=
nts out a fascinating dynamic: boys in the show behave very differently tow=
ard male versus female authority figures=E2=80=94and it lines up with what =
we see in real life.</p></li><li><p><span>I reflect on </span><a href=3D"ht=
tps://www.robkhenderson.com/p/the-unspeakable-truth-about-children" rel=3D"=
">my visit to the Michaela School in London</a><span>, which stands in star=
k contrast to the chaos we see in </span><em>Adolescence</em><span>. </span=
></p></li><li><p><span>The show references Andrew Tate as a toxic influence=
 on young males. We ask whether a character like Jamie=E2=80=94the boy at t=
he center of </span><em>Adolescence</em><span>=E2=80=94would behave the sam=
e way in a world without Andrew Tate.</span></p></li><li><p>William makes t=
he case that the mainstream media=E2=80=99s tendency to lump incels, red-pi=
llers, and Andrew Tate into a single bucket misses important distinctions=
=E2=80=94and leads to real confusion among adults.</p></li><li><p>I compare=
 the Andrew Tate phenomenon to the way 50 Cent and Eminem were received in =
the early 2000s=E2=80=94adults panicking, kids idolizing. </p></li><li><p>W=
e dig into the psychological power of humiliation and how it fuels status-s=
eeking violence in young men.</p></li><li><p>William explained why =E2=80=
=9Cincel=E2=80=9D isn=E2=80=99t just a description of being involuntary cel=
ibate=E2=80=94it=E2=80=99s an identity built around fatalism, resentment, a=
nd a belief in the dominance of looks in the dating market.</p></li><li><p>=
I found William=E2=80=99s theory compelling=E2=80=94that incel ideology mig=
ht be an unconscious strategy to manipulate the mating market: convince riv=
als to give up, lower women=E2=80=99s self-esteem, and improve one=E2=80=99=
s mating prospects.</p></li><li><p><span>William explained why many incels =
may not be high in the Dark Triad traits like psychopathy or narcissism=E2=
=80=94but score very high on something else: </span><a href=3D"https://link=
.springer.com/article/10.1007/s40806-022-00336-x" rel=3D"">interpersonal vi=
ctimhood</a><span>; a tendency to ruminate on slights, demand validation of=
 your suffering, and believe you=E2=80=99re morally superior because you=E2=
=80=99ve been wronged</span></p></li><li><p>We talked about how video games=
 can hijack male status drives=E2=80=94offering rewards and goals without t=
he discomfort of real-life struggle or rejection.</p></li><li><p>William br=
ought up the =E2=80=9Cick=E2=80=9D factor=E2=80=94how women often see video=
 games as antisocial or juvenile, especially when it feels like their partn=
er is disappearing into a screen.</p></li><li><p>We discussed how VR and se=
x robots might be the next evolutionary mismatch=E2=80=94supernormal stimul=
i that hijack male mating psychology.</p></li><li><p>Even when sex is avail=
able=E2=80=94via escort, OnlyFans, or robot girlfriend=E2=80=94it=E2=80=99s=
 not satisfying. What most men, most people, actually want is to feel desir=
ed.</p></li><li><p>William mentioned a German study where 9% of men reporte=
d using sex dolls=E2=80=94a surprisingly high number, considering their cos=
t and stigma.</p></li><li><p>Much more in this wide-ranging conversation. L=
et me know what you thought of this discussion in the comments.</p></li></u=
